name: Ethan Sharp
text: This is the Section 8 office. I believe that the Section 8 program needs to be cut completely. I worked in this office and saw the fraud first hand. There is a problem when individuals are bragging about having their 5th child just because it is going to make their rent go down. Section 8 has become a crutch and has enabled people to solely love off the tax payers money. They don't want to work because the government supplies them with their every need. It's sickening! The manager of this office is also impossible to work for. As white man I felt discriminated against on a daily basis. The Section 8 program is bad news. I would never rent to any of them.

name: Amanda Hall
text: The manager of this complex is prejudice and i was told by Several neighbors and employees that she especially doesn't like white people . She has been HARASSING me since i moved in. They "inspect" my apt 2-3 times a month! She is always threatening to cancel my lease. In fact she is trying to kick me and my son out on the street. She makes up lies. But i record EVERYTHING. This is NOT going to end the way she wants it to. My son graygraduates this year. As soon as he does we're leaving! I would rather be homeless all by myself than put up with her constant lies and threats. And all because I'm a white woman!?!? That's just wrong!! They do abuse the ceap out of their authority! So if you have ANY other option, i recommend you take it. Otherwise you're in for a very rough fight.

text: I went in to simply get a list of local apartments. The short, white female at the front desk had an unpleasantly odd smirk on her face as she talked down upon me. I don’t think she realizes that I have a very good job, nor an extensive college transcript and I am going to school to be a Nurse, and then after that I will become a future Nurse Practitioner. I happened to be looking for an apartment while I work with my realtor to find a house for sale in the area. I assume her name is Karen. We all know a “Karen”, right? Well, whatever your name is, shame on you. Thanks for making society a smaller place, and making yourself feel better for working in a small building surrounded by the same people you “help” who may be having a rough time, but somehow some of those will go on to do great things. Unlike you, I believe that every single person has the chance of becoming something great and doing extraordinary things. Have a wonderful day and please get an attitude check as you somehow work your way back down to Earth.

name: Amber Townson
text: Made me pay for repairs, including;  the "drain" fail in ny bathroom floor. Backing up water from every shower and even sewer. Dirty and clogged A/C unit, even though I had JUST moved in at the time. Mold is taking over and it's bad in my a/c unit. We aren't allowed to have a bedroom lock nor bathroom lock, which means my toddler can walk in on us having sex. They never give you dates in advance on when things are going to be done. They rushed around last year in a frenzy to make things look "good" for the HUD inspection, but if they would had kept up with their maintenance all year then they wouldn't be having to rush and do their job and inconvenience the tenants. I caught a maintenance man in my purse one morning when he came to change my filter. I called him out on it even and he lied even though I seen him with my own eyes! I also have had several pieces of lingerie missing and so has my neighbor. No use of complaining about that because it's my word against theirs. The mowers have also put 2 chips in the windshield of my car and they are refusing to pay to have it fixed because the mowers are "under a contract". I have a career with and know all about gov't contracting and this place is breaking many rules. If it wasn't for being knocked down as soon as I get money saved, we would had been out of here a year ago. I don't recommend this place.

name: Joe “THE GREAT JOSSIAH” Thompson
text: Great office management and great maintenance staff!

name: La Donna Griffin
text: If I could give it no stars, I would.  Have treated me so wrong,, unfair treatment.   Put other people who have never been tenants here in the brand new apartments, when I put in request for them, & had letters from my Neurologist because I am disabled and have serious health issues.  They were made like I need apartment to be,,forced to carry groceries and stuff in, not able to, causing me more, unnecessary pain, Especially after surgery.  They charge for repairs, maintenance calls,, not supposed to, no other place does this,, it's landlords responsibility. Do inspections, tell you where to put your furniture, judge your housekeeping, yet they do nothing to fix up apartment, black mold, cracks in walls, paint peeling, weeds growed up, so many problems. Remodeled my neighbors kitchen, yet haven't done mine, probably won't , unfair. Need a new, better executive director,, who is fair, will do things right,, & this is supposed to be for low income people,,yet too many tenants aren't,, have expensive, new vehicles, some have 2-3 vehicles. Healthy, people put it new, & remodeled handicap accessible apartments, when I was supposed to be, fair housing, & American Disability Act.  I could go on about how bad it is,, how bad & unfair I've been treated,, it's actually called abusing me, emotional and mental abuse,,& physical, .
